description: {"blocks":[{"key":"35koh","text":"The DNA extraction protocol presented below is based on the FISH DNA extraction protocol developed in the Eco-AlpsWater Project (https://www.alpine-space.org/projects/eco-alpswater/deliverables-final/dt1.1.2.--8.2-fish_dna_extraction_vigidna.pdf), adapted from the NucleoSpin® Soil kit (MACHEREY-NAGEL) according to the study of Pont et al (2018).","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":60,"length":28}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":129,"length":116}],"data":{}},{"key":"abdsf","text":"The methodology described here is the extraction of DNA, from eDNA samples collected with filtration cartridge adapted to treat large volume of water (e.g. VigiDNA® 0.45-μm capsule). The cartridge is stored at -20°C until extraction (no preservation buffer is added).","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":183,"length":14},{"style":"bold","offset":207,"length":8}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4oh9u","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8drsk","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"8E9DD02A508511ED929F0A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.alpine-space.org/projects/eco-alpswater/deliverables-final/dt1.1.2.--8.2-fish_dna_extraction_vigidna.pdf"}}}}

Ingenieurbüro™))","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5dgu1","text":"-A microcentrifuge for 1.5 to 2 mL tubes (relative centrifugal force ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d9de8","text":"-5/10 mL pipette + tips 5/10 mL status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"9s48c","text":"-Wear gloves throughout the extraction process","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7teka","text":"-Clean the bench with DNA off or 10% commercial bleach before and after manipulation","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"30fsl","text":"-Use tips with filters to avoid contaminations","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"93n91","text":"-All steps have to be performed under a specific DNA-work station (sterile area equipped with air filtration and UV systems). ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":1,"length":125}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"475qn","text":"-If possible work in a room equipped specifically for rare/degraded DNA (i.e. room equipped with positive air pressure, UV treatment, frequent air renewal, and accessible only with full protective clothing and mask). in any case the extraction can be done in a room were PCR products are amplified","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":1,"length":71}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8oo47","text":"Sample preparation","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":18}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"52mk7","text":"Add 50 mL of the mild lysis buffer to the frozen filtration capsule and store them for 2 h at 4°C","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"blfa5","text":"Agitate the filtration capsule for 15 min on a flask shaker at 800 rpm","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"871hv","text":"Collect 30 mL of buffer from the filtration capsule and divide it equally in two 50 mL tubes (15 mL each)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3j7uo","text":"Add 33 ml of absolute ethanol and 1.5 mL of 3M sodium acetate to the 50 mL tubes","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e1a52","text":"Store the tubes at least one night at -20°C","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9ht3e","text":"Centrifuge the tubes at 4,000 x g for 15 min at 6°C","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7kp7c","text":"Discard the supernatant, resuspend the pellet and merge it into one tube","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: The following part of the protocol is reported exactly as described in the FISH DNA extraction protocol developed in the Eco-AlpsWater Project
